? OptimalTempMin

= 390

? OptimalTempMax
Upper end of bell curve for determining heat based rate reactions
= 450
ExplodeTemp
? ExplodeTemp
Temperature at which reaction explodes - If any reaction is this hot, it explodes!
= 800
OptimalpHMin
? OptimalpHMin
Lowest value of pH determining pH a 1 value for pH based rate reactions (Plateu phase)
= 8
OptimalpHMax
? OptimalpHMax
Higest value of pH determining pH a 1 value for pH based rate reactions (Plateu phase)
= 10
ReactpHLim
? ReactpHLim
How far out pH wil react, giving impurity place (Exponential phase)
= 3
CatalystFact
? CatalystFact
How much the catalyst affects the reaction (0 = no catalyst) [NOT IMPLEMENTED YET]
= 0

? CurveSharpT

= 1

? CurveSharpH
How sharp the pH exponential curve is (to the power of value)
= 1

? ThermicConstant

= 5

? HIonRelease

= 0.02

? RateUpLim

= 1

? FermiExplode
If the chemical explodes in a special way
- No

? PurityMin
